Line21.6D03F: Their battle would leave the world a wasteland. And whoever won would show no mercy to what was left.
Line23.6D03F: Our only hope was to reach Lilith before Inarius, but we couldn’t have predicted what happened next.
Line19.6D03F: But what we didn’t know was that while we were lost in the swamp, Inarius and the Cathedral were launching a campaign to strike at Lilith.
Line17.6D03F: Astaroth and the deal, Rathma and the key...it had all been leading to this.
Line15.6D03F: We needed answers, and we got them. Lilith was poised to storm the very gates of Hell.
Line3.6D03F: Did I make the right choice? I did what I had to.
Line1.6D03F: A strange thing, knowing where you’ll go when you die. One less damn mystery to worry about, at least.
